  "prompt": "Will Biharis ever get respect in India?",
  "response": "The question of respect for any particular group of people, including Biharis, in India is complex and influenced by various social, economic, and historical factors. While Bihari culture and contributions are significant, biases and stereotypes can persist. Efforts to foster understanding, awareness, and appreciation for diverse cultures within India can help improve the perception of Biharis and promote respect.\n\nEncouraging positive narratives, celebrating achievements, and addressing socio-economic challenges faced by any community plays a crucial role in changing perceptions over time. Ultimately, respect can be cultivated through education, open dialogue, and mutual understanding among different communities in India.",
